ğŸ¯ Goal:

Let users search for found documents that others have reported â€” so if someone lost a license, they can see if anyone found it.

ğŸªœ Step 1: Create File

Inside the same project folder, create
ğŸ“ search_found.php

ğŸªœ Step 2: Add This Code

Paste this ğŸ‘‡

<?php include('includes/db_connect.php'); ?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Search Found Document</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h2>Search Found Document</h2>

  <form method="POST" action="">
    <input type="text" name="search" placeholder="Enter document type or number..." required>
    <button type="submit" name="submit">Search</button>
  </form>

  <hr>

  <?php
  if (isset($_POST['submit'])) {
      $search = $_POST['search'];

      $sql = "SELECT * FROM found_documents 
              WHERE doc_type LIKE '%$search%' 
              OR doc_number LIKE '%$search%' 
              OR description LIKE '%$search%'";

      $result = $conn->query($sql);

      if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
          echo "<h3>Search Results:</h3>";
          echo "<table border='1' cellpadding='10'>
                  <tr>
                    <th>ID</th>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Document Type</th>
                    <th>Document Number</th>
                    <th>Contact</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                    <th>Date</th>
                  </tr>";
          while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
              echo "<tr>
                      <td>{$row['id']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['name']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['doc_type']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['doc_number']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['contact']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['description']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['date']}</td>
                    </tr>";
          }
          echo "</table>";
      } else {
          echo "<p style='color:red;'>No matching found documents found.</p>";
      }
  }
  ?>
</body>
</html>

